      "content": "Your feelings of being a burden are valid and common among parents navigating severe health declines, but choosing to withdraw from your children or let them feel \"forced\" to help may cause them more lasting emotional pain. While your immediate impulse to be less demanding stems from deep love and a desire to protect them, this pain management strategy could inadvertently create guilt or distance where your connection once flourished. It is worth considering that framing your needs as unfair shows your kids how to handle their own caregiving stress, so seeking support through therapy, respite care, or adult social networks might offer relief without sacrificing your relationship.",
