      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the profound pain behind your question, and the desire for your children to breathe freely is a testament to a love that went so far it threatens to define its own end. While the instinct to let go feels noble, choosing self-sacrifice over shared grief often leaves families with fragmented bonds that heal much more slowly than intact ones. It is important to remember that your presence, even in struggle, still supports their sense of legacy and that their lives aren't stolen until you decide to leave them. Please be gentle with yourself as you navigate this; you matter enough to advise that there are support resources specifically for caregivers nearing a decision point, and they might offer a different perspective on \"letting go.\"",
